          <from>MS. PAM BIRDSALL</from>
          <p>MS. PAM BIRDSALL : Madam Speaker, I am very happy to be able to stand today and talk about this bill. The arm's-length arts council has been something that our community has wanted for a very long time, and it has to be noted that in March 2002 the arts council was dissolved. That was a council that took almost two decades to be formed, and with all the members of the arts community of Nova Scotia working very hard to have that happen.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
